news.title: Gurugram: Amrapali homebuyers feel NBCC Green View tremors
news.para: The company, however, assured a bench of Justices U U Lalit and Bela M Trivedi that the PSU was committed to maintaining quality of construction and the controversy surrounding the Gurugram project should not be linked with Amrapali projects.

news.title: Provided information sought by Enforcement Directorate: Indiabulls Housing
news.para: The company said the ECIR (Enforcement Case Information Report) registered by ED stems out of an FIR filed by one Ashutosh Kamble, who is part of a long-running extortion and blackmail racket against the firm.

news.title: China's Zhenro Properties slumps after debt warning
news.para: Zhenro said in a filing late on Friday that its internal funds available for debt servicing have become increasingly limited since the announcement it made on Jan 4 about the redemption, citing adverse market conditions.

news.title: Rents reach 'insane' levels across US with no end in sight
news.para: In the 50 largest U.S. metro areas, median rent rose an astounding 19.3% from December 2020 to December 2021, according to a Realtor.com analysis of properties with two or fewer bedrooms.

news.title: Evacuation from Gurugram's NBCC Green View and handover by March 1
news.para: In his order, Yadav said, “As the nodal officer, Batth will supervise handover of the project to the developer for carrying out repairs and evacuation of residents from the society by March 1.”

news.title: Aurangabad, Latur, Nanded & Parbhani civic bodies to get stamp duty surcharge
news.para: The money corresponds to 1% surcharge recovered by the state town planning department on stamp duty paid towards different property transactions during the year 2021-22 in order to generate funds for infrastructure development in these cities.

news.title: RWAs meet Haryana CM, raise structural problems in societies
news.para: ​​The members also raised structural problems in various residential complexes and demanded structural audits be made mandatory for all housing societies.

news.title: Mumbai: ED went to search Indiabulls Housing, 'prevented' by court stay
news.para: On Monday morning, several teams of ED landed at different premises of Indiabulls group companies to search their premises in a money laundering case related to purchase of land parcels in the Palghar district long ago.

news.title: Maharashtra: To change housing society name in records, collector's nod not must
news.para: ​Justices Shahrukh Kathawalla and Milind Jadhav quashed and set aside a February 16, 2021 letter of the City Survey Officer (CSO), Chembur, refusing to mutate the name of Basant Vihar CHSL in revenue records for want of an NOC from the collector.

news.title: Commercial real estate market gains momentum in Gujarat
news.para: According to data from the Gujarat Real Estate Regulatory Authority (GRERA), new commercial project registrations in Gujarat rose by 24% to 213 in 2021-22, against 171 in 2020-21.

news.title: Rajasthan government to extend cut-off date for regularising colonies
news.para: According to an official, the government is planning to extend the last date for applications seeking regularisation of houses constructed on agricultural land in urban areas to December 31, 2018.

news.title: Bengaluru urban district has 6,000 illegal layouts
news.para: The Administrative Reforms Committee-2, which is headed by former chief secretary TM Vijay Bhaskar, said that many measures are needed to control the growth of unauthorised layouts.

news.title: No GST on leasing residential building as hostel: Karnataka HC
news.para: The lessee leased out the six-floor property with 42 rooms as hostel for providing long-term accommodation to students and working professionals with the duration of stay ranging from 3 months to 12 months.

news.title: IIT Madras researchers to identify new housing tech, help bring down construction costs
news.para: ​The 'Accelerator Affordable Sustainable Housing Accelerators' is an initiative of the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs to provide incubation and acceleration support to potential future technologies that are not yet market-ready (pre-prototype applicants) or to the technologies that are market-ready (post-prototype applicants).

news.title: Kerala CM to hand over keys of 320 houses
news.para: In the first phase construction of 222 houses was completed and keys were handed over to the beneficiaries. Construction of 320 houses was completed in the second phase of RAY spending Rs 33.79 crore.
